    "recipeInstructions": [
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.thespruceeats.com/thmb/0RET879hRyfzhtRilgDfAgfx5i8=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/easy-saffron-rice-recipe-3217204-step-01-331c0a12e0424fedaf8ccd15a818708a.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Gather the ingredients."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.thespruceeats.com/thmb/QBhvJk52R7FyVRbJwL72vU4jfr4=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/easy-saffron-rice-recipe-3217204-step-02-2801a067f84b464da6ecd6c4a5f0c2e4.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Pour the stock into a medium-sized pot with a tight-fitting lid. Place the pot on the stove over high heat."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.thespruceeats.com/thmb/3pgllES-KCAvCIn4S9T1Wefse20=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/easy-saffron-rice-recipe-3217204-step-03-d7475ac4b57741ba9ddd84435ac44777.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "While theÂ stock is coming to a boil, add the turmeric, saffron, chile (if using), and a squeeze of lemon or lime juice. Stir well."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.thespruceeats.com/thmb/b-690KI3cJSjM2gwIR1EvYdqF_Y=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/easy-saffron-rice-recipe-3217204-step-04-c21aee8c04764ee3b666d13fb55a7b43.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Add the rice plus 1 1/2Â tablespoons fish sauce (or 1/4 teaspoon salt) and stir. Bring to a boil."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.thespruceeats.com/thmb/sBB-EeUfPqrtkbga3S7kGw-zrdk=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/easy-saffron-rice-recipe-3217204-step-05-e1f832ed9c3246799c5be2794ba30d2b.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Reduce the heat to low and cover tightly with a lid. Cook 12 to 15 minutes, or until liquid has been absorbed by the rice. (Insert a fork or knife straight down into the pot and push the rice aside. If you see liquid, it still needs more time to cook.)"
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.thespruceeats.com/thmb/PwaHrUl10-FR1O8k-SwzquCBAgo=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/easy-saffron-rice-recipe-3217204-step-06-c9e7981fee0848c7bdec5690d615add8.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "When most of the liquid is gone, turn off the heat and place the lid on tightly. Allow the pot to remain on the burner for another 5 to 10 minutes, or until you&#39;re ready to eat. The residual heat inside the pot will finish steaming the rice. The rice will stay warm in this way for 1 hour or more."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.thespruceeats.com/thmb/myDp2u5WgHzGHbAqfkmyXxoJ_fA=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/easy-saffron-rice-recipe-3217204-step-07-4b6d1ec8f20a4fdbb9ea62e8b6e6190e.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Before serving, remove the lid and fluff rice with chopsticks or a fork. Taste test for salt, adding 1/2 tablespoon more fish sauce or a little more salt if needed (the amount will depend on the saltiness of your stock). If the rice tastes too salty, add another squeeze of lemon juice."
        }
    ],
